   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-accepting" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-accepting-acceptted" mid="39" select_type="3" />
      <talk_question mid="5"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Vernicka is lost in his thoughts.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-a" mid="40" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="6"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>But if I think about it, I find it strange. Hiver is a newborn Child and Grele is a mutant who was powerful enough to kill </FONT><FONT color=#a82424>Tryan</FONT><FONT color=#662500> when he was just born. But you said Hiver could kill Grele.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-b" mid="41" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>You realised that only now? Well, you saw it for yourself. If Hiver wants Grele to die, he would willingly slit his own throat.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-c" mid="42" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Then what should we do? What should I do…?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-d" mid="43" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Phew... don't despair so easily, my immature friend. Saying "Hiver can hurt you" wouldn't help at all in persuading Grele. Hiver has become the meaning of life for him.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-e" mid="44" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>If we want to persuade him, we need to take the approach of saying "there's a way to turn Hiver back to normal" or tell Grele that "it is dangerous because he can hurt his sister". The latter is probably more powerful.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-f" mid="45" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Grele can hurt Hiver? But he said he would even give up his life for his sister. How can that be possible?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-g" mid="46" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>According to researches by the Anti-Goddess Faction, there's only a fine line between <FONT color=#a82424>mutants</FONT> and <FONT color=#a82424>Childs</FONT>. Whether you can keep your human sanity with your own will or be completely devoured by the Child side is what determines the outcome.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-h" mid="47" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Does that mean if Grele loosens up a little and his Child side takes over his consciousness, he can kill Hiver?!</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-i" mid="48" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>…You see?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-j" mid="49" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>No one knows whether a Child's persona would really go out of control. But the moment you heard what I said, you began to be suspicious of the "possibility".</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-k" mid="50" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Uh... Oh... Wow….!!</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-l" mid="51" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Anxiety stems from possibility and fear burns with ignorance. How much fire you can make with the spark I gave you is all up to you.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-l" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-m" mid="52" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>I get you. <BR>But I'm worried Grele might meet Hiver before I see him again.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-m" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-n" mid="53" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Hmm... Did you say Grele felt Hiver's energy from the <FONT color=#a82424>Strange Devices</FONT> and was investigating on them? Then both Grele and Hiver are likely to be moving in the same path following those devices.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-n" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2" mid="54" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Why did Hiver install such devices in the first place? That's something we have to check up on.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
